cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use this software in academic or research work, or if you reference
  a novel algorithm, result, or empirical finding from this repository,
  please cite it as below. GitHub renders a "Cite this repository" button
  that reads this file. A machine-readable BibTeX/APA export is available
  from that button.
title: "TurboQuant-MLX Core"
abstract: >-
  Near-lossless weight and KV cache compression for large language models
  on Apple Silicon, implemented as fused Metal kernels via the MLX
  framework. Implements the TurboQuant algorithm (Zandieh et al.,
  ICLR 2026) with additional engineering for hybrid-attention
  architectures, per-layer adaptive codebooks, and symmetric-by-origin
  codebook validation.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Kovshilovsky
    given-names: Eugene
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-04-17"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - quantization
  - weight compression
  - kv-cache compression
  - apple-silicon
  - mlx
  - metal
  - large language models
  - lloyd-max
  - turboquant
references:
  - type: article
    title: "TurboQuant: Nearly-Lossless Randomized Quantization of LLM Weights and Activations"
    authors:
      - family-names: Zandieh
        given-names: Amir
    year: 2026
    notes: "ICLR 2026; algorithm reference for the core quantization method."
